Title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Trailer
Comment:
Just days before this trailer arrived I remember eagerly waiting for this first look... That excitement and wondering how the graphics are gonna look like. Mind you this is the first R* game that was built from ground up for current-gen consoles. And prior to this, we had no idea how a next-gen (now current-gen) R* game was gonna look like.

Nevertheless the game didn't disappoint on the graphics front, in fact, it far exceeded my expectations. So rich in attention to detail, this will hold the best looking open-world game title for years to come. Can't wait to play again on PC in a few days.

Title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Trailer
Comment:
There is no doubt in my mind the delay was due to lack in console power. They had to wait for the release and consumption of Xbox One X to avoid an hilarious graphics downgrade controversy.
Despite them saying it was delayed to ensure a better player experience, games aren't delayed for an entire year to fix bugs. They had to wait for the release of xbox one x, which is why there's a very excact year amount of time which coincides very well with the release and shipping of the xbox one x. 
This isn't a hit at rockstar, I'm glad they are delaying it rather than releasing a downgraded version of the game. It's a hit at the gaming industry as a whole and the fact that games quality is determined by ancient hardware of consoles that do little but hold them back. Take a look at games like star citizen or total war and weep at what could be if all games were made for pc.
Games would have looked like this in 2010 if it weren't for consoles.

Title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Trailer
Comment:
If this doesn't come out for PC with PS4 and XONE, forget it. It won't come out for PC ever.
Now, the ports are REALLY easy to make. PC and console use the same x86-64 architechture. There is no reason to "delay" a port, because there is no longer Sony's Cell CPU crap to deal with, nor there is a Power-PC to deal with. In theory, the only thing that differs from one to another is the operating system - which is not much different if you compare XONE with PC (Both run Windows) and the PS4 is slightly different.
If there is no PC version, I will borrow an XBOX from a friend and buy the game. I would rather play it on PC as the graphics are much better (the consoles are already outdated in hardware) but if it doesn't come out on PC, I will consider borrowing a console just to play this specific game.

Title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Trailer
Comment:
"The game‚Äôs vast and atmospheric world will also provide the foundation for a brand new online multiplayer experience"

Worried. RDRO was amazing, and had more going for it than GTAO currently does, in my *opinion*. Really hoping we dont end up with a neutered/sterilized/watered-down experience this time around. Same goes for single-player. I initially hated that V removed so much of the little things, the details that made San Andreas so immersive such as weight/muscle mass/melee fighting styles etc etc. I expect them to at *least* keep all the systems and features that were present in RDR's single-player mode and then build upon them with current tech and trends.

Two steps forward NO steps back please! Thanks for reading my blog

Title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Trailer
Comment: Almost 7 years ago, I was a legend of the west. Legendary 5 level 50, platinum trophy, 100% completion on base and undead nightmare, number 17 in the world for Fort Mercer hideout, when the game died, something died inside of me, my friends moved on, and I was alone in this game. Now, seven years on, I am a different man, and my teen years of gaming are being brought back to me. my whole teenage life was spent playing this game with my friends, all in a massive posse, I hope this game brings back those feelings, and fun that I once had with them. I hope Rockstar create the right atmosphere for this game and don't use GTA V as it's base, this game, needs to be different than that.

Title: Red Dead Redemption 2 Trailer
Comment:
My thoughts: Some immediate complaints I have (not to be greedy):
- It would be nice if the game ran at 1080p @60 fps on PS4 and Xbox One. A game's technical capacity certainly isn't everything. However, you would think a publisher as accomplished as Rockstar would aim for 60fps with new titles. 
- A PC VERSION. As a PC gamer (and big fan of Rockstar), it's incredibly disappointing to see no PC version alongside the console versions. After GTA V's PC-port 2-year wait, it seems obvious that Rockstar is greedy (to a certain extent) and prioritizes their profits over their loyal fans. Although it's self-explanatory, all gamers should have an equal chance to buy and play their desired games.
